[]: Akagi Family and Casper Theory: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by Maya Ibuki &raquo; Wed May 30, 2012 6:58 am Let me start off by introducing this scene: Rei I&#39;s death. Depending on which version of the sub or dub you view, Naoko strangles Rei with something along the lines of &#39;You&#39;re the same as me.&#39; I know this is referring to the fact the just like Rei, Naoko can be &#39;replaced&#39;, however what I&#39;m puzzled about is that she knew / considered the possibility of Gendo having sexual relationships with others. Now, we know that even though Ritsuko and Naoko had a professional relationship, Ritsuko also despised her mother &#40;I&#39;m assuming dyeing her hair is something to consider&#41;. Here&#39;s just a theory I came up with , which only applies to the TV continuity. PERHAPS Ritsuko and Gendo were hooking up beforehand, and probably Naoko knew about this, which is why she delivers that line about being a substitute. Now, the MAGI was based off Naoko as a mother, woman and a scientist. Now, as we all know Casper, who represents Naoko as a &#39;woman&#39;, betrayed Ritsuko during EoE, when Ritsuko decided to initiate the self-destruction system. Either way, it was inevitable the Instrumentality project would reach it&#39;s climax, but perhaps &#39;Casper&#39; was watching over Ritsuko and Gendo, and thus, betrayed Ritsuko in order for her to suffer the shooting - as at this point, I believe Naoko knew what was going on between Ritsuko and Gendo before and after her death. I think &quot;You&#39;re the same as me.&quot; suggests a link to the theory that Naoko was also the &#39;soul&#39; for Unit-00. Just some random blabble I thought of.[/img]

